First, we need to install This application [Jira Spoke].
Navigate > Applications/Plugin > Jira Spoke

Next step is, we need to make credentials to connect with Jira.
Now Create new Credentials and First we need to create new Jira API Token because that API we can use as a password when making new Credentials.

Now we need to make a connection [I am creating HTTPs Connection].
 
We need to Fill all these details: -
Name
Credential
Connection alias
Connection URL
Now Submit it.

4.	Now next we need to look at the credentials and connections.
 
Now we move to Flow Designer
Create New
Name: - Jira Test Integration HUB
 
Add Trigger: -
 
Add Action: -
Fill this fields: -
Action
Project ID
Issue Type ID
Summary
Description
Priority
Now Add New action to update record.

Now need to check the connection, create a new record and check the execution.

 

 





